    <h4>Top Driver: tenure (0.4781)</h4>
    <p>This is the single strongest predictor of churn in your dataset. Customers with low tenure are at substantially higher risk. Targeted onboarding and early engagement programmes for new customers could significantly reduce this risk.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="insight-box">
    <h4>2nd Driver: Contract (0.3879)</h4>
    <p>Contract type is strongly associated with churn. Month-to-Month customers leave at much higher rates than customers on 1- or 2-year contracts. Offer incentives to convert to longer-term plans as a priority retention action.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="insight-box">
    <h4>3rd Driver: TotalCharges (0.3071)</h4>
    <p>Total charges reflect the combined effect of tenure and monthly charges. Lower total charges often indicate newer customers with less investment in the service relationship.</p>
